cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method for automated segmentation of brain tumors in MRI images using machine learning techniques such as fully convolutional networks and random forests. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of hand-crafted features and the evaluation on a medical imaging dataset suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the use of multimodal MRI images may also make this paper relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
